raw_data.title: Project Manager
raw_data.description: Primary responsibility for project management on specific projects assigned. Duties include budget and schedule control, organization or overall project team to ensure project deliverables are identified and executed.

raw_data.title: QA/QC Manager/Inspector
raw_data.description: Coordinate and ensure the necessary project controls, management, and inspection to ensure the overall quality of the project. Review construction documents, IT/AV system specifications, security designs, furniture designs, and other technical documents to identify quality concerns and methods to ensure compliance with the approved design.

raw_data.title: Senior Cost Estimator
raw_data.description: Perform detailed cost estimating including design, construction, furniture, IT/AV systems, security systems, and other components of the modern commercial office environment. Prepare cost estimate reports and Independence Government Estimated when acting on behalf of the Government. Identify value engineering alternatives to reduce initial cost and/or overall life cycle costs. Perform cost-benefit analyses to assist in selection of various options.

raw_data.title: Senior Scheduler
raw_data.description: Prepare critical path method (CPM) schedules, including all project tasks, including design, construction, furniture, IT/AV systems, security systems, and other components of the modern commerical office environment. Monitor the schedule during the project and update periodically as required. Identify time impacts and prepare mitigation strategies. Analyze delays to identify responsible parties.

raw_data.title: CAD Technician
raw_data.description: Utilize computer aided design (CAD) software to develop or edit drawings. Take field measurements and examine conditions to produce as-built drawings. Incorporate multiple layers to organize various disciplines. Perform CAD design under the supervision of a project manager or interior designer.

raw_data.title: Principal
raw_data.description: Primary responsibility for coordination and oversite of contracts including project management, cost estimating, CPM scheduling, and claims analysis. Principal is responsible for negotiating and executing subcontracts, retaining employees including hiring as necessary, and providing high level support of DB senior staff. The Principal is responsible for successful delivery of services to the customer while managing subcontractors and employees.
